<DocLayout title="Research & Policy" description="AEGIS published papers, standards engagement, and policy positions advancing governance-first AI safety.">
  <h1>Research &amp; Policy</h1>

  <p>
    The AEGIS Initiative engages with policymakers, standards bodies, and the
    research community to advance governance-first approaches to AI safety. Our
    work spans peer-reviewed publications, formal standards submissions, and
    responses to emerging policy proposals.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Published Papers</h2>
    <p>
      Four papers submitted to IEEE, NIST, and NCCoE covering constitutional
      governance architecture, threat modeling, risk management frameworks, and
      AI agent identity. Preprints are available on Zenodo with peer-reviewed
      versions linked when published.
    </p>
    <p><a href="/research/papers/">View all published papers &rarr;</a></p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Standards Engagement</h2>
    <p>
      Active engagement with NIST AI RMF, IEEE journals, and the NCCoE AI Agent
      Identity &amp; Access Management project. AEGIS contributes formal position
      papers and technical submissions to shape emerging AI governance standards.
    </p>
    <p><a href="/research/standards/">View standards engagement &rarr;</a></p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Policy Positions</h2>
    <p>
      Responses to emerging policy proposals and regulatory frameworks that
      affect AI governance, safety, and security. Includes engagement with
      White House AI frameworks and congressional proposals.
    </p>
